HEADWORD: checkage
<hw>check"age</hw> <pr>(ch⟦ecr⟧k"⟦asl⟧j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of checking; <as>as, the <ex>checkage</ex> of a name or of
an item in a list</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The items, or the amount, to which attention is
called by a check or checks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>checked</ent>⟦br⟧
